  '<h2 id="migrations">Migrations <a class="anchor" href="#migrations">#</a></h2>',
  '<p><code>b.migrations</code> applies versioned schema files at boot, holds a cluster-wide advisory lock so only one replica runs the wave, and refuses to start the app if a migration goes from "applied" to "missing on disk".</p>',
  '<h3>Migration file shape</h3>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">{',
  '  up:           (db) =&gt; void,              // required: true — synchronous DDL/DML',
  '  description:  string,                    // default: filename',
  '}</code></pre>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">// migrations/0007-page-publish-state.js',
  'module.exports = {',
  '  up: function (database) {',
  '    database.run("ALTER TABLE pages ADD COLUMN publishedAt INTEGER");',
  '    database.run("CREATE INDEX idx_pages_published ON pages(publishedAt)");',
  '  },',
  '};</code></pre>',
  '<p>No <code>down</code> by default — operators that want reversible migrations write the inverse as the next migration, which keeps the audit trail honest. Each applied migration writes a row to <code>_blamejs_migrations</code> with a SHA3-512 of the file content; if the file changes after application, boot refuses with a checksum mismatch.</p>',

  '<h2 id="seeders">Seeders <a class="anchor" href="#seeders">#</a></h2>',
  '<p><code>b.seeders</code> is for content the framework or app needs at boot: default roles, country lists, the wiki\'s own landing pages.</p>',
  '<h3>Seeder file shape</h3>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">{',
  '  description:  string,                    // required: true',
  '  envs:         string[],                  // default: inferred from path',
  '  rerunnable:   boolean,                   // default: false — UPSERT on every boot',
  '  dependsOn:    string[],                  // default: [] — sibling seed names',
  '  run:          (db, ctx) =&gt; Promise,      // required: true',
  '}</code></pre>',
  '<p>Rerunnable seeders UPSERT on every boot — useful while iterating on copy. One-shot seeders apply once and record their fingerprint. Forward-only: seeders have no <code>down()</code> inverse — operators reset by truncating the seeded tables themselves.</p>',
  '<p><code>ctx</code> carries <code>{ env, runner, clock }</code> so seeds can invoke other framework primitives without re-importing them. Cycles in <code>dependsOn</code> + missing deps are caught at load.</p>',

  '<h2 id="atomic-file">Atomic file writes <a class="anchor" href="#atomic-file">#</a></h2>',
  '<p><code>b.atomicFile</code> is the crash-safe file-write primitive every framework component that touches disk uses. Write to <code>&lt;target&gt;.tmp</code>, <code>fsync</code> the file, atomically <code>rename</code> over the target. A power-loss mid-write leaves either the OLD bytes or the NEW bytes intact, never a half-written file.</p>',
  '<h3>Surface</h3>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">b.atomicFile.writeJson(path, value)        // → byteCount',
  'b.atomicFile.writeBuffer(path, buf)         // → byteCount',
  'b.atomicFile.readJson(path)                 // → parsed value | null',
  'b.atomicFile.readSync(path)                 // → Buffer',
  'b.atomicFile.lock(path, fn)                 // serialize fn() per-path</code></pre>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">await b.atomicFile.writeJson("./data/feature-flags.json", flags);',
  'await b.atomicFile.writeBuffer("./data/binary.bin", Buffer.from(payload));',
  '',
  '// Lock-and-modify pattern for read-modify-write workflows',
  'await b.atomicFile.lock("./data/counter.json", async function () {',
  '  var counter = await b.atomicFile.readJson("./data/counter.json") || { n: 0 };',
  '  counter.n += 1;',
  '  await b.atomicFile.writeJson("./data/counter.json", counter);',
  '});</code></pre>',

